    Task

    Contact Lumenary via Email

    As a potential customer, I click the contact email to reach out for inquiries, so that I can initiate communication with Lumenary for assistance or information.

    Success definition: Given I am on the Lumenary homepage When I click on 'contact@lumenary.com' Then I should see my email client open or be prompted with options to get in touch with Lumenary.

By clicking the email address, I am triggering the functionality expected from an email link to ensure that the user's email client opens, allowing them to compose a message to Lumenary. This directly advances the task of initiating contact.

    Action: click('contact@lumenary.com') # Attempting to click the contact email again to see if it opens an email client or provides more information.

    Change Description: After clicking on the contact email 'contact@lumenary.com', either an email client was opened or additional interface elements related to contacting Lumenary were displayed, as indicated by the change in content surrounding the email address while the overall structure of the webpage remained intact.
